Technical Consistency Checks — Validity, Range, Format, Uniqueness (UK)

Perimeter: Final RDS population
Objective:
To confirm that all variables included in the RDS comply with basic technical rules (format, valid ranges, uniqueness), are interpretable without ambiguity, and can be safely used for estimation, validation, and supervisory review without manual correction.
________________________________________
1. Identifier, Scope, and Reference Fields
Variables
•	Borrower_ID
•	Date
•	Portfolio
•	Segment
•	Internal_sector
•	GROUP_CODE
Format & validity checks
•	Borrower_ID
o	Must be non-null
o	Must be unique per borrower
o	Must not change over time for the same legal entity
•	Date
o	Valid date format
o	Must correspond to month-end
o	No dates outside Dec-2020 to Dec-2024
•	Categorical fields (Portfolio, Segment, Internal_sector)
o	Values must belong to a closed and documented domain
o	No free text, spelling variants, or legacy codes

Example check:
Verify that Segment only contains approved values for the FIRB Corporates Other / SME perimeter and that no unexpected categories appear historically.
________________________________________
2. Exposure, Balance, and Amount Variables (Monetary)
Variables
•	Total_Exposure
•	final_group_expsr
•	Turnover
•	Balance
•	Arrears
•	All Min / Max / Avg balance and arrears variables
•	Bureau monetary variables (net_worth, cc_gb_24, etc.)
Range checks
•	Must be numeric
•	Must not contain text, symbols, or formatting characters
•	Expected sign:
o	Exposure, balances, arrears → ≥ 0
o	Net worth → can be negative, but within plausible bounds
•	Extreme values:
o	Identify implausible magnitudes (e.g. balance >> total exposure, turnover orders of magnitude above peers)
Example checks
•	Balance ≤ Total_Exposure
•	Arrears ≤ Balance
•	final_group_expsr ≥ Total_Exposure when GROUP_CODE is populated
•	Flag values above the 99.9th percentile for review
________________________________________
3. Default, NPL, Forbearance, and Status Flags
Variables
•	Default, Default_12m
•	re_npl, np_npl, wo_npl, ff_npl, dr_npl, su_npl*, npl_probation, fb_probation
Format & validity checks
•	Must be binary (0/1, Y/N or equivalent)
•	No nulls unless explicitly justified
•	No unexpected values (e.g. 2, -1, “Yes”, blank)
Example check:
Verify that all default and NPL flags only take values in {0,1} and that missing values are explicitly justified as “not applicable” rather than data gaps.
________________________________________
4. Financial Ratios (Core, SME, CCT, CCB)
Variables
All ratio variables, including:
•	GC_Ratio_*
•	CCT_Ratio_*
•	SME_Ratio_*
•	CCB_Ratio_*
•	Ratio_37
Range & plausibility checks
•	Must be numeric
•	Identify:
o	Division-by-zero artefacts
o	Extreme absolute values (very large positives or negatives)
•	Expected economic ranges (indicative, not hard caps):
o	Liquidity ratios: typically ≥ 0
o	Leverage ratios: typically ≥ 0, but may spike with low denominators
o	Profitability ratios: negative values possible, but not unbounded
Example checks
•	Flag ratios with absolute values above predefined thresholds (e.g. |ratio| > 1,000)
•	Identify cases where denominator is close to zero
•	Confirm whether negative numerator/denominator combinations are explicitly allowed and documented
________________________________________
5. Moving Averages (MA_*) and YoY Variables
Variables
•	MA_*
•	YOY_*
Format & range checks
•	Must be numeric
•	Should not exist when insufficient history exists
•	YoY values:
o	Check for technical placeholders (e.g. -99)
o	Confirm that extreme YoY values are not artefacts of near-zero denominators
Example checks
•	MA variables should be missing if fewer than two valid historical observations exist
•	YoY values outside a reasonable band (e.g. > ±1,000%) flagged for review
________________________________________
6. Behavioural Counts, Durations, and Percentages
Variables
•	DPD
•	MonthsSince_*
•	Consec_*
•	Count_*
•	PCT_*
Range & format checks
•	Count / duration variables:
o	Integer
o	≥ 0
•	Percentage variables:
o	Numeric
o	Expected range: 0–100 (or 0–1 if explicitly defined so)
Example checks
•	PCT_ArrGT30_12m ∈ [0,100]
•	MonthsSince_DPDGT90 ≥ 0
•	No negative counts or percentages >100
________________________________________
7. Qualitative Questionnaire Variables
Variables
•	SMEQL_RQS_*
Format & domain checks
•	Must belong to the defined scale (e.g. -2 to +2)
•	No free text or unexpected values
•	Check for:
o	Excessive concentration at neutral (e.g. 0)
o	Missing vs neutral clearly distinguishable
Example check:
Confirm that qualitative scores only take values in {-2, -1, 0, 1, 2} and that missing values are not implicitly encoded as neutral.
________________________________________
8. Bureau Scores and Categorical Bureau Flags
Variables
•	credit_rat
•	comm_delphi_scr
•	CC_GB_04, cc_gb_34
•	Other bureau indicators
Format & validity checks
•	Scores:
o	Numeric
o	Within provider-defined range
•	Flags:
o	Closed set of allowed values
o	No undocumented codes

Example check:
Validate that credit_rat values fall within the official Experian scale and that any missing or blank values have a documented semantic meaning.
________________________________________
9. Uniqueness and Duplicate Records
Variables involved
•	Borrower_ID
•	Date
Uniqueness checks
•	One record per Borrower_ID per Date
•	No duplicate rows with identical keys
•	No multiple ratings per borrower per month unless explicitly justified

Example check:
Verify that there are no duplicate records for the same Borrower_ID and Date combination in the RDS.
________________________________________
10. Consistency with Data Dictionary
Applies to
•	All variables
Checks
•	Variable name, definition, unit, and sign must match the Data Dictionary
•	No undocumented transformations
•	No reused variables with changed meaning
Example check:
Confirm that all ratio variables are expressed in the units and direction described in the approved Data Dictionary and have not changed definition over time.
